pics including exploration, scientific rationality, the occult, medical instruments, patents, communication, and infrastructure, the contributors situate Canadian scientific and technological developments within larger national and transnational contexts. The first major collection of its kind in thirty years, Made Modern explores the place of science and technology in shaping Canadians’ experience of themselves and their place in the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aScience and civilization. 0aSciencexSocial aspectszCanadaxHistory. 0aSciencezCanadaxHistory. 0aTechnological innovationszCanadaxHistory. 0aTechnology and civilization. 0aTechnologyxSocial aspectszCanadaxHistory. 0aTechnologyzCanadaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh1 aAdcock, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdcock, Tina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBocking, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGucciardo, Dorotea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHadlaw, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHull, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones-Imhotep, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones-Imhotep, Edward, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJØrgensen, Dolly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKranakis, Eda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacfarlane, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobertson, Beth A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSera-Shriar, Efram, econtributor.4